File: Eskom has announced load reduction in several provinces. Pixabay/DevoKit JOHANNESBURG -  Eskom will be implementing load reduction in Limpopo and the North West on Thursday, to avoid network overloading in high-density areas. The power utility said load reduction will take place between 5pm and 9pm. READ: Eskom fraud case postponed to June Areas like Mopani District, Sekhukhune and Rustenburg Sector will be affected by the load reduction. Provincial statements issued by Eskom name the specific areas that will be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
